<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Hotspots and Dead Zones</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Bingo · Scrabble Words Finder · English Solver</p>


      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The Scrabble board isn't uniform. At any point during a game, some areas are goldmines of scoring potential while others are wastelands. Learning to read the board — instantly identifying where the points are and where they aren't — is what separates club players from tournament players.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Identifying Hotspots</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">A hotspot is any board position where a high-scoring play is available. Here's what creates them:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Unused Premium Squares with Access</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A TW square is only a hotspot if there's a path from existing tiles to reach it. Count the empty squares between the nearest tile and the premium — if it's reachable in one play, it's live.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 Hook Positions on High-Value Words</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">An existing 8-letter word with an unhoooked front or back position is a hotspot. Adding one letter scores for the full perpendicular word you play through that spot.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⬛ Open Parallel Lanes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A row adjacent to an existing word where 3+ valid 2-letter cross-words are possible. Parallel plays stack points from each cross-word formed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📏 7+ Empty Squares in a Lane</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Any row or column with 7+ consecutive empty squares connecting to existing tiles is a bingo lane. These are the highest-value hotspots on the board.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Timing Matters</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Hotspots are <span class="text-white font-medium">time-sensitive</span>. If you don't exploit a hotspot on your turn, your opponent likely will. When you spot a hotspot that's reachable by both players, either use it immediately or block it — never leave it open unless you have no choice.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Identifying Dead Zones</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Dead zones are areas where no significant scoring is possible. Recognising them saves time and prevents wasted turns:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚫 Consumed Premium Squares</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Once a TW or DW is used, the area around it drops in value dramatically. Premium squares only activate on the turn they're first covered — never again.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧱 Blocked Lanes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Areas surrounded by tiles on all sides with no hook positions. No word can enter or exit the zone. These typically form in the centre after 10+ turns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚠️ Trap Zones</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Areas that LOOK promising but opening them gives your opponent better access. A dead zone for you might be a hotspot for your opponent — and vice versa.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Board Scanning Technique</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Develop a systematic scanning habit during your opponent's turn:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 The 4-Step Board Scan</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Premium squares:</strong> Locate all unused TW and DW squares. Trace a line from the nearest existing tile — can it be reached in one play?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Hook spots:</strong> Check every word on the board — can a letter be added to front or back? Especially near premium squares.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Bingo lanes:</strong> Count consecutive empty squares in every row and column touching existing tiles. Mark lanes with 7+ spaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Parallel lanes:</strong> Which rows let you play alongside existing words forming multiple cross-words? These compound your score.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/board-openness-control/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Board Openness Control — when to open or close the board</span>
          </a>
