      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Creating Hotspots for Yourself</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Advanced players don't just read the board — they shape it. You can engineer hotspots that only benefit your specific rack while appearing neutral to your opponent.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Leave vowels exposed near TWS:</span> If you hold consonant-heavy tiles that pair well with vowels (like SH, TH, ST), play a word that leaves a vowel near a triple word square lane.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Create hook spots only you can fill:</span> If you hold the J and the board has no JO/JA/JI spot, create one by playing a word that exposes an O near a premium square.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Open bingo lanes for your stem:</span> If you hold SATIRE, play a short word that opens a 7-square lane. Your opponent won't know you've engineered a setup play.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/board-openness-control/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:border-amber-300 dark:hover:border-amber-700 hover:bg-amber-50/50 dark:hover:bg-amber-900/10 transition-all group">
